# import all the necessary libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import warnings

# import raw data
historical_data_total = pd.read_csv('combined_data_cleaned.csv', index_col=0)
historical_data_total.index = pd.to_datetime(historical_data_total.index)
regime_classification = pd.read_excel(
    'regime_classification.xlsx', index_col=0)
regime_classification.index = pd.to_datetime(regime_classification.index)
ticker_list = pd.read_excel('list_of_bloomberg_symbols_complete.xlsx')
In [ ]:
# select first 4 columns of regime_classification
regime_classification = regime_classification.iloc[:, :4]

# record all disinflation regimes
start_time = []
end_time = []
for i in range(len(regime_classification) - 1):
    if regime_classification['Disinflation'][i] == False and regime_classification['Disinflation'][i + 1] == True:
        start_time.append(regime_classification.index[i])
    if regime_classification['Disinflation'][i] == True and regime_classification['Disinflation'][i + 1] == False:
        end_time.append(regime_classification.index[i])
end_time.append(regime_classification.index[-1])

disinflation_period = pd.DataFrame(
    {'start_time': start_time, 'end_time': end_time})

# ticker list for equity, fixed_income and currency
ticker_list_equity = ticker_list[ticker_list['category'] == 'Equities']
ticker_list_fixed_income = ticker_list[ticker_list['category']
                                       == 'Fixed Income']
ticker_list_currency = ticker_list[ticker_list['category'] == 'Currencies']

# calculate the 1 day log return of
historical_log_return = np.log(historical_data_total).diff()
historical_log_return = historical_log_return.dropna(how='all')

# plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
# historical_log_return['SPX Index'].plot()
# plt.show()

historical_data_equity = historical_log_return[ticker_list_equity['ticker']].dropna(
    how='all')
historical_data_fixed_income = historical_log_return[ticker_list_fixed_income['ticker']].dropna(
    how='all')
historical_data_currency = historical_log_return[ticker_list_currency['ticker']].dropna(
    how='all')
SPX = historical_log_return['SPX Index'].dropna(how='all')

# plot equity
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
plt.title('Equity')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Log Return')
plt.plot(historical_data_equity)
plt.legend(historical_data_equity.columns)
plt.show()

# plot fixed income
historical_data_fixed_income = historical_data_fixed_income.iloc[:, ::-1]
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
plt.title('Fixed Income')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Log Return')
plt.plot(historical_data_fixed_income)
plt.legend(historical_data_fixed_income.columns)
plt.show()

# plot currency
historical_data_currency = historical_data_currency.iloc[:, ::-1]
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
plt.title('Currency')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Log Return')
plt.plot(historical_data_currency)
plt.legend(historical_data_currency.columns)
plt.show()

# plot SPX
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
plt.title('SPX')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Log Return')
plt.plot(SPX)
plt.show()

# mean, variance, and sharpe ratio for equity by sector
equity_by_sectors = pd.DataFrame()
for i in range(len(ticker_list_equity)):
    if ticker_list_equity['subcategory'].iloc[i] == 'Sector':
        equity_by_sectors = equity_by_sectors.append(
            pd.DataFrame({'ticker': ticker_list_equity['ticker'].iloc[i],
                          # annualized
                          'mean': equity_disinflation[ticker_list_equity['ticker'].iloc[i]].mean() * 252,
                          'variance': equity_disinflation[ticker_list_equity['ticker'].iloc[i]].var() * 252,
                          'sharpe_ratio': equity_disinflation[ticker_list_equity['ticker'].iloc[i]].mean() / equity_disinflation[ticker_list_equity['ticker'].iloc[i]].std() * np.sqrt(252)}, index=[0]), ignore_index=True)

# plot TR grouped bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
equity_by_sectors_TR = equity_by_sectors.iloc[:11]
equity_by_sectors_TR = equity_by_sectors_TR.sort_values(
    by='sharpe_ratio', ascending=False)
equity_by_sectors_TR.plot(x='ticker', kind='bar', figsize=(20, 10))
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.xlabel('Tickers')
plt.ylabel('Annualized')
plt.title('Equity by Sectors Total Return')
plt.show()

# plot level1 grouped bar chart
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
equity_by_sectors_level1 = equity_by_sectors.iloc[-11:]
equity_by_sectors_level1 = equity_by_sectors_level1.sort_values(
    by='sharpe_ratio', ascending=False)
equity_by_sectors_level1.plot(x='ticker', kind='bar', figsize=(20, 10))
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.xlabel('Tickers')
plt.ylabel('Annualized')
plt.title('Equity by Sectors')
plt.show()

# mean, variance, and sharpe ratio for currency
currency = pd.DataFrame()
for i in range(len(ticker_list_currency)):
    currency = currency.append(
        pd.DataFrame({'ticker': ticker_list_currency['ticker'].iloc[i],
                      'mean': currency_disinflation[ticker_list_currency['ticker'].iloc[i]].mean() * 252,
                      'variance': currency_disinflation[ticker_list_currency['ticker'].iloc[i]].var() * 252,
                      'sharpe_ratio': currency_disinflation[ticker_list_currency['ticker'].iloc[i]].mean() / currency_disinflation[ticker_list_currency['ticker'].iloc[i]].std() * np.sqrt(252)}, index=[0]), ignore_index=True)

print(currency)
